summary: Email chain discussing the handling of document processing in US v. Epstein case, specifically regarding the return of 56 DVDs containing case data and review of vendor work product before uploading to Relativity.

events.title: Document processing completion notification
events.description: Vendor completed document unitization and coding of data from 56 DVD files in the US v. Epstein case, with arrangements being made for return of DVDs and review of work product.

keyFacts: Vendor completed processing of data from 56 DVD files related to the US v. Epstein case.
The processed data was ready for review before being uploaded to Relativity document management system.
The email chain shows coordination between legal team members regarding handling of case materials in November 2019.
